The All Progressives Congress (APC) has finally zoned its chairmanship slot to the North-Central and position of national secretary to the South-West ahead of the March 26 national convention. After dilly-dallying for a while, the party released the zoning formula on Wednesday afternoon. NIGERIA DAILY: How Genotype Tests Put Families In JeopardySix Nigerian airlines form historic alliance Can Aivoji Turn Around The Fortunes Of Lagos PDP? Major Highlights Of Independent Newspapers Awards It said during its regular meeting on March 8, 2022, the Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) of the party approved the recommendations of the Committee on Zoning. The details are below: NORTH-CENTRAL: Benue, Kogi, Kwara, Nasarawa, Niger and Plateau States SOUTH-SOUTH: Akwa Ibom, Bayelsa, Cross River, Delta, Edo and Rivers States POLL SOUTH – WEST: Ekiti, Lagos, Ogun, Ondo, Osun and Oyo States SOUTH-EAST: Abia, Anambra, Ebonyi, Enugu and Imo States PMQs: Johnson Struggles To Defend Refugee Policy Lagos Junior League, Nath Boys Made Me Who I Am Today –… NORTH – EAST: Adamawa, Bauchi, Borno, Gombe, Taraba and Yobe States NORTH -WEST: Jigawa, Kaduna, Kano, Katsina, Kebbi, Sokoto and Zamfara States